    "body": "In the device code in `rolling_detail.cuh`, there are variables declared as `volatile` to work around compiler optimizations in CUDA 10.x. E.g.:\r\n```c++\r\n    // declare this as volatile to avoid some compiler optimizations that lead to incorrect results\r\n    // for CUDA 10.0 and below (fixed in CUDA 10.1)\r\n    volatile cudf::size_type count = 0;\r\n```\r\nGiven that CUDF 0.20 supports CUDA 11.0+, it should now be safe to remove this comment, and the `volatile` attributes.\r\n\r\nIf not handled in #8158, this can be addressed after #8158 is merged.",
